    "caption": "The biggest nose in the jungle, and it's loud.",
    "shortDescription": "Proboscis monkeys live in the mangrove forests of Borneo, and the males grow enormous drooping noses that hang down over their mouths. When a male honks to attract a mate or warn rivals, that big nose amplifies the sound like a built-in megaphone. Fun fact: Proboscis monkeys have partially webbed feet and are strong swimmers — they regularly cross rivers and have even been seen swimming in the ocean."
